                        <interp inst="t18560303-370-offence-2" type="offenceSubcategory" value="forgery"></interp>The prisoner was also charged upon four other indictments with forging and uttering other acceptances:</rs> to all which he</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">PLEADED GUILTY</hi>. Aged 32.</p>
               <p>(<hi rend="italic">Joseph Sounders, a fanner of Collingwood, in Buckinghamshire; and Henry Morton, builder and plasterer, of Uxbridge, gave the prisoner a good character).—<rs id="t18560303-370-verdict-2" type="verdictDescription">
